&#xa0;[bold]Written evidence submitted by[bold] [bold]the Charity Commission[bold] [CT 15][bold]Introduction[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]How Charities Might Be Abused [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]“
[normal]Countries should review the adequacy of laws and regulations that relate to entities that
[normal] 
[normal]can
[normal] 
[normal]be abused for the financing of terrorism.
[normal] 
[normal]Non-profit organizations are particularly vulnerable, and countries should ensure that they cannot be misused:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]a)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]by terrorist organizations posing as legitimate entities;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]b)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]to exploit legitimate entities as conduits for terrorist financing, including for the purpose of escaping asset freezing measures; and
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]c)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]to conceal or obscure the clandestine diversion of funds intended for legitimate purposes to terrorist organizations”
[normal]. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Extent of the risk and evidence of abuse[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Reducing the ability of terrorists to abuse charities[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Awareness
[normal] 
[normal]- 
[normal]raising awareness in the sector to build on charities’ existing safeguards
[normal]Oversight and Supervision
[normal] – proactive monitoring of the sector, analysing trends and profiling risks and vulnerabilities 
[normal]Co-operation
[normal] – strengthening partnerships with government regulators and law enforcement
[normal] 
[normal]agencies both nationally and internationally
[normal] 
[normal]Intervention
[normal] – dealing effectively and robustly when abuse, or the risk of ab
[normal]use
[normal], is apparent
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Co-operation with law enforcement  [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The international dimension - working with [bold]other governments [bold]on investigations[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]The international dimension [bold]&#xad;[bold]- supporting other governments and multi-laterals[bold]&#xa0;
